title: finns scones
description: pretty nice scones!
source: my friend finn the scone guy
---
§recipe
  §ingredients
	450g flour (about 890ml)
	around like 10 grams of baking powder?
	around 100g raisins (if u want)
	50g room temperature butter
	300ml milk
	1-2 egg yolk (optional)
  §/ingredients
  
  §instructions
	preheat the oven at 250°c i think
	mix the flour, baking powder and raisins
	add in the butter and press it in well (ideally until its all perfectly combined)
	add the milk and mix
	knead it
	add flour if its not the right texture (im not sure whats the right texture but it shouldnt stick)
	roll out the dough to ~2.5cm (1 inch)
	cut out the scones and put them on a baking tray. you dont need paper or anything normally
	glaze them with the egg yolk (optional but they look really fancy)
	put in the oven for maybe 10 minutes. check regularly
  §/instructions
§/recipe
